Within about 1 minute after his encounter with █████ and █████, ██████ was seen passing through the second-floor offices. In his hand was a full "Coke" bottle which he had purchased from a vending machine in the lunchroom. He was walking toward the front of the building where a passenger elevator and a short flight of stairs provided access to the main entrance of the building on the first floor. Approximately 7 minutes later, at about 12:40 p.m., ██████ boarded a bus at a point on Elm Street seven short blocks east of the Depository Building. The bus was traveling west toward the very building from which ██████ had come. Its route lay through the Oak █████ section in southwest ██████, where it would pass seven blocks east of the roominghouse in which ██████ was living, at 1026 North ██████████████. On the bus was Mrs. Mary Bledsoe, one of ██████'s former landladies who immediately recognized him. ██████ stayed on the bus approximately 3 or 4 minutes, during which time it proceeded only two blocks because of the traffic jam created by the motorcade and the assassination. ██████ then left the bus. A few minutes later he entered a vacant taxi four blocks away and asked the driver to take him to a point on North ██████████████ several blocks beyond his roominghouse. The trip required 5 or 6 minutes. At about 1 p.m. ██████ arrived at the roominghouse. The housekeeper, Mrs. ███████████████, was surprised to see ██████ at midday and remarked to him that he seemed to be in quite a hurry. He made no reply. A few minutes later ██████ emerged from his room zipping up his jacket and rushed out of the house.

Approximately 14 minutes later, and just 45 minutes after the assassination, another violent shooting occurred in ██████. The victim was Patrolman J. D. ██████ of the ██████ police, an officer with a good record during his more than 11 years with the police force. He was shot near the intersection of 10th Street and █████████████, about nine-tenths of a mile from ██████'s roominghouse. At the time of the assassination, ██████ was alone in his patrol car, the routine practice for most police patrol officers at this time of day. He had been ordered by radio at 12:45 p.m. to proceed to the central Oak █████ area as part of a concentration of patrol car activity around the center of the city following the assassination. At 12:54 ██████ radioed that he had moved as directed and would be available for any emergency. By this time the police radio had broadcast several messages alerting the police to the suspect described by ███████ at the scene of the assassination -- slender white male, about 30 years old, 5 feet 10 inches and weighing about 165 pounds.

At approximately 1:15 p.m., ██████ was driving slowly in an easterly direction on East 10th Street in Oak █████. About 100 feet past the intersection of 10th Street and █████████████, ██████ pulled up alongside a man walking in the same direction. The man met the general description of the suspect wanted in connection with the assassination. He walked over to ██████'s car, rested his arms on the door on the right-

