The suspect █████ was about to question in connection with the assassination of the President and the murder of a policeman was born in New Orleans on October 18, 1939, 2 months after the death of his father. His mother, ██████████ Claverie ██████, had two older children. One, ████████, was a half-brother to ███ from an earlier marriage which had ended in divorce. The other was ██████ ██████, a full brother to ███ and 5 years older. When ███ ██████ was 3, Mrs. ██████ placed him in an orphanage where his brother and half-brother were already living, primarily because she had to work.

In January 1944, when ███ was 4, he was taken out of the orphanage, and shortly thereafter his mother moved with him to ██████, Tex., where the older boys joined them at the end of the school year. In May of 1945 ██████████ ██████ married her third husband, ███████████████. While the two older boys attended a military boarding school, ███ lived at home and developed a warm attachment to ██████, occasionally accompanying his mother and stepfather on business trips around the country. ███ started school in Benbrook, Tex., but in the fall of 1946, after a separation from ██████, ██████████ ██████

